yingyinNormal.en: I don't eat honey. No problem. I'll eat the honey.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不吃蜂蜜。那没关系，我自己吃。

yingyinNormal.en: You want get something to eat?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你想吃点东西吗?

yingyinNormal.en: They'd eat their own children.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们连自己的孩子都吃。

yingyinNormal.en: Can I have something else to eat?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我能不能吃点别的？

yingyinNormal.en: We could eat after the movie.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们可以看完电影再吃晚饭。

yingyinNormal.en: Please don't eat on the tour. Is that her?
yingyinNormal.zh: 别在这里吃东西。是她吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, well, I'll just, go eat by myself.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，那我就自己一个人去吃了。

yingyinNormal.en: Don't we have anything to eat here? Nothing?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这里没有吃的吗?什么都没有?

yingyinNormal.en: I understand. You eat when you are upset.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我明白你的心思，不开心的时候就吃。

yingyinNormal.en: What's a midnight feast? We eat things in secret.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么是午夜大餐？我们偷偷吃东西。

yingyinNormal.en: Sheldon, are you hungry? I could eat. Let's go.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢尔顿，你饿吗？我想吃点东西。我们走。

yingyinNormal.en: Eat? My dinner? In your apartment? Yeah. Why not?
yingyinNormal.zh: 吃？我的晚饭？在你家？是啊，怎么了？

yingyinNormal.en: What's the sauce? Is it meat based? No. Eat now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是什么酱，是肉酱吗？不是的，快吃吧。

yingyinNormal.en: You must take off those muddy clothes before you eat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在吃冰淇淋之前，得把脏衣服给脱掉。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah. Some eat meat, some eat vegetable.
yingyinNormal.zh: 确实，有人吃肉，也有人吃素。

yingyinNormal.en: Don't make me eat you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不要逼我吃掉你!

yingyinNormal.en: Eat Riley! Okay. But no biting.
yingyinNormal.zh: 把莱丽吃掉！好吧，但不许咬。

yingyinNormal.en: Did you eat all the neighbor candy?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你吃掉给邻居们的糖果了吗？

yingyinNormal.en: I was thinking we would eat around four.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我打算4点左右开始吃饭。

yingyinNormal.en: You just eat your dinner here while you're waiting.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你可以一边等，一边吃饭。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>

derivative_info_list.mean: n. 食者；吃… 的人；可生吃的苹果

examination_example.sentence: The country produces only about 60 per cent of the food it <highlight>eats</highlight>, down from almost three-quarters in the late 1980s.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 该国的粮食产量仅占其所食用粮食的60%左右，低于上世纪80年代末的近四分之三。

examination_example.sentence: Families don't sit down to <highlight>eat</highlight> together as frequently as before.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一家人不像以前那样经常坐在一起吃饭了。

examination_example.sentence: You won't be <highlight>eating</highlight> out a lot, but once every few months treat yourself to a set lunch at a good restaurant.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你不会经常外出就餐，但每隔几个月，请自己去一家不错的餐厅吃一顿午餐。

examination_example.sentence: Meanwhile, Schwitzgebel—who had predicted no effect—will be <highlight>eating</highlight> his words.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他曾预言没有效果——将收回他的话。

examination_example.sentence: Embarrassing scandals and the popularity of the republican left have forced him to <highlight>eat</highlight> his words and stand down.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 令人尴尬的丑闻和受到欢迎的共和党左派迫使他食言并下台。

sense_info_list.en: worry or cause anxiety in a persistent way

examination_example.sentence: In my guidelines for saving the environment, I suggest modest changes, like <highlight>eating</highlight> vegetarian meals two days a week.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在我的环保指南中，我建议做一些适度的改变，比如每周两天吃素食。

examination_example.sentence: Some claim that you want to force everyone to <highlight>eat</highlight> a vegetarian diet and make private transport illegal.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一些人声称，你想强迫所有人吃素，并将私人交通定为非法。

examination_example.sentence: The second group, called micro bats, are smaller in size and mostly <highlight>eat</highlight> insects.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 第二类称为微型蝙蝠，体型较小，主要以昆虫为食。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Eating</highlight> a balanced breakfast helps to up our energy, as well as make up for protein and calcium used throughout the night.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 吃上一顿营养均衡的早餐，有助于弥补我们夜间所消耗的能量，以及蛋白质和钙。

examination_example.sentence: A review of 54 studies found that <highlight>eating</highlight> breakfast can improve memory, though the effects on other brain functions were inconclusive.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一篇对54项研究的文献综合分析发现，吃早餐可以改善记忆，但对大脑其他功能的影响尚无定论。

examination_example.sentence: Their babies retain the ability to produce their own chlorophyll, though they can't generate energy from sunlight until they've <highlight>eaten</highlight> enough algae to steal the necessary genes, which they can't yet produce on their own.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们的后代延续了这种可以自己制造叶绿素的能力，尽管直到它们吃掉足够多的藻类以获取这种必要的基因(它们还无法自己制造这种基因)，它们才能够从阳光中制造能量。

examination_example.sentence: There are a lot of studies on the relationship between breakfast eating and possible health outcomes, but this may be because those who <highlight>eat</highlight> breakfast choose to habitually have health-enhancing behaviours such as regular exercise and not smoking.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 关于吃早餐与可能的健康结果之间的关联，有很多研究，但这可能是因为那些吃早餐的人通常会选择有益健康的习惯和行为，比如不抽烟、经常做运动。

examination_example.sentence: Those who made breakfast the largest meal of the day were more likely to have a lower body mass index (BMI) than those who <highlight>ate</highlight> a large lunch or dinner.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与吃了大量午餐或晚餐的人相比，那些把早餐作为一天中最f丰盛一餐的人更有可能拥有较低的身体质量指数(BMI)。

examination_example.sentence: By prescribing nutritional changes or launching programs such as ‘ Shop with your Doc, they are trying to prevent, limit or even reverse disease by changing what patients <highlight>eat</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 通过规定营养变化或推出“与您的医生一起购物”之类的计划，他们正试图通过改变患者的饮食来预防，限制甚至逆转疾病。

examination_example.sentence: Should you <highlight>eat</highlight> food fallen on the floor then?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 那么你应该吃掉在地上的食物吗？

examination_example.sentence: It's still worth investigating food myths like this one because they shape our beliefs about when food is safe to <highlight>eat</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 像这样的食物神话还是值得研究的，因为它们塑造了我们对食物何时可以安全食用的信念。

word_usage.usage: eat不可与形容词delicious连用，因为delicious本身就是“吃起来可口”的意思。
eat作为动词的基本意思是指“吃”，但是表示“吃药”，一般说take medicine或have medicine，不说eat medicine。

examination_example.sentence: People who <highlight>eat</highlight> slowly tend to consume about 70 fewer calories (卡路里) per meal than those who rush through their meals.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 吃得慢的人往往比那些匆匆忙忙吃饭的人每餐少消耗约70卡路里的热量。
